WEBVTT

00:05.923 --> 00:06.882
[Saul] Previously
on Homeland...

00:06.965 --> 00:09.843
You start executing
men in a stadium,

00:09.927 --> 00:11.386
you could be setting off
a wave of violence

00:11.470 --> 00:13.555
that'll destabilize
your whole country.

00:13.639 --> 00:16.141
And we have an opportunity
to crush them

00:16.225 --> 00:17.059
once and for all.

00:17.142 --> 00:20.687
We must have the strength
to do it.

00:32.908 --> 00:35.327
[Carrie] Any word on Max?
JSOC's still looking, right?

00:35.410 --> 00:36.537
Not on the ground.

00:36.620 --> 00:38.413
[groaning]

00:38.497 --> 00:40.207
[gunshot]

00:40.290 --> 00:41.583
‐ Saul...
‐ We're doing what we can do.

00:41.667 --> 00:43.168
That's bullshit.
I sent him in there.

00:43.252 --> 00:44.670
I want a favor.

00:44.753 --> 00:46.797
One of our people went missing
near the crash site.

00:46.880 --> 00:49.341
You lied about your interaction
with Yevgeny Gromov.

00:49.424 --> 00:50.884
You are vulnerable
to him in ways

00:50.968 --> 00:53.929
neither of us can imagine.

00:54.012 --> 00:56.265
Max is still out there.

00:56.348 --> 00:58.517
Yevgeny has a lead on him.
He just sent word.

00:58.600 --> 01:01.812
In 30 minutes, you will be
escorted to a plane.

01:02.562 --> 01:06.525
You will go willingly
or in handcuffs.

01:06.608 --> 01:08.569
♪ tense music ♪

01:08.652 --> 01:14.741
♪♪♪

01:19.037 --> 01:21.748
‐ [siren wailing]
‐ [man] Get back, get back!

01:21.832 --> 01:25.294
[indistinct shouting]

01:25.377 --> 01:28.463
♪ disquieting music ♪

01:28.547 --> 01:30.674
♪♪♪

01:30.757 --> 01:32.634
[man] The World Trade Center,
Tower Number One

01:32.718 --> 01:36.013
is on fire!

01:36.096 --> 01:38.265
[Carrie] I missed something
once before. I won't‐‐

01:38.348 --> 01:40.183
I can't let that happen again!

01:40.267 --> 01:43.895
An American prisoner of war
has been turned.

01:43.979 --> 01:45.230
You're a disgrace
to your nation,

01:45.314 --> 01:46.523
Sergeant Nicholas Brody.

01:46.606 --> 01:48.442
You're a traitor
and a terrorist,

01:48.525 --> 01:51.528
and now it's time
to pay for that.

01:51.611 --> 01:53.739
Are you accusing me
of something?

01:53.822 --> 01:55.741
[Yevgeny]
You really do not remember?

01:55.824 --> 01:57.409
[Carrie]
Remember what?

01:57.492 --> 01:59.911
[Jim] We may be dealing with
a compromised officer here.

01:59.995 --> 02:01.621
[Saul] You had a relationship
complicated enough

02:01.705 --> 02:04.041
to lie about.

02:04.124 --> 02:05.625
[Carrie]
Yeah, it's complicated.

02:05.709 --> 02:07.252
I lost seven months
of my life.

02:07.336 --> 02:08.879
To my Russian handler?

02:08.962 --> 02:11.673
[man]
Is our strategy working?

02:11.757 --> 02:14.426
[Saul] And you will become
the focus of an investigation

02:14.509 --> 02:17.554
that will define
the rest of your life.

02:17.638 --> 02:19.681
[Carrie] That not every
problem in the Middle East

02:19.765 --> 02:22.392
deserves a military solution.

02:22.476 --> 02:27.022
Because this whole country
went stupid crazy after 9/11.

02:27.105 --> 02:28.899
[Jim]
Carrie, you're not yourself.

02:28.982 --> 02:31.109
[Carrie] I'm still putting
the pieces together.

02:31.193 --> 02:36.073
[Saul] Please, God,
tell me you have it.

02:36.156 --> 02:37.866
♪♪♪

02:37.949 --> 02:39.451
[man]
Is there no fucking line?

02:39.534 --> 02:41.662
[Saul]
I believe you.

02:41.745 --> 02:43.830
No one else will.

02:46.958 --> 02:50.712
♪ light music ♪

02:50.796 --> 02:56.093
♪♪♪

03:10.899 --> 03:15.445
So I get my wish.

03:15.529 --> 03:18.907
To travel the streets
of Kabul one more time

03:18.990 --> 03:22.077
without hiding.

03:22.160 --> 03:25.872
It's not over.

03:27.457 --> 03:28.250
After G'ulom releases your men

03:28.333 --> 03:31.086
and they're safely
out of the city,

03:31.169 --> 03:34.047
we'll throw the spotlight
on you, your trial.

03:34.131 --> 03:38.343
G'ulom is the government now.

03:38.427 --> 03:40.303
He'll have to behave
with the whole world watching.

03:40.387 --> 03:43.640
G'ulom doesn't care
what the world thinks.

03:43.723 --> 03:48.437
♪♪♪

03:48.520 --> 03:50.689
[indistinct radio chatter]

03:56.486 --> 03:58.530
Haissam...

03:59.781 --> 04:02.993
I'm ready.

04:08.165 --> 04:10.542
[quiet radio chatter]

04:29.561 --> 04:31.229
[overlapping chatter]

04:31.313 --> 04:34.775
[Saul] You have
an opportunity here.

04:34.858 --> 04:37.486
Show the world what justice
means in your country now.

04:37.569 --> 04:41.156
We called the Taliban savages
when they executed people

04:41.239 --> 04:43.074
in this stadium 20 years ago.

04:43.158 --> 04:45.619
Show us things have changed.

04:45.702 --> 04:46.745
What has changed?

04:46.828 --> 04:48.663
Not the Taliban.

04:48.747 --> 04:51.500
Not America.

04:51.583 --> 04:55.253
Still not understanding
anything about us

04:55.337 --> 04:57.756
even after all these years.

04:57.839 --> 04:59.633
[man] Khalifa! Khalifa!

04:59.716 --> 05:02.260
[overlapping chatter]

05:02.344 --> 05:04.805
speaking Pashto

05:15.607 --> 05:18.360
Those are his people.
They control half your country.

05:18.443 --> 05:20.028
If you don't treat him
with respect,

05:20.111 --> 05:24.616
your world will explode.

05:24.699 --> 05:27.494
Give him a fair trial.

05:27.577 --> 05:29.454
[indistinct chatter continues]

05:29.538 --> 05:32.541
♪ tense music ♪

05:32.624 --> 05:37.671
♪♪♪

06:00.277 --> 06:03.071
[indistinct radio chatter]

06:04.739 --> 06:07.075
[indistinct chatter]

06:18.128 --> 06:20.505
[indistinct chatter]

06:22.841 --> 06:24.885
One second.

06:26.678 --> 06:28.179
[whispered]
Jenna...

06:28.263 --> 06:30.724
Saul.

06:33.560 --> 06:35.478
I took Carrie
to the airport last night

06:35.562 --> 06:38.607
for her flight to Germany
as you asked.

06:38.690 --> 06:40.233
I escorted her to the gate,

06:40.317 --> 06:42.527
watched her
walk down the jetway‐‐

06:42.611 --> 06:43.862
[Mike]
To make a long story short,

06:43.945 --> 06:45.322
she never got on the plane.

06:45.405 --> 06:46.948
Instead, she takes off
with a GRU officer.

06:47.032 --> 06:49.618
Who else?
Yevgeny Gromov.

06:49.701 --> 06:52.162
I don't know if she's been
working with him since Russia,

06:52.245 --> 06:53.913
or they just
ran into each other here,

06:53.997 --> 06:56.625
or she pulled
a Ken Philby or what.

06:56.708 --> 06:57.792
‐ Where are they?
‐ Who knows?

06:57.876 --> 07:00.879
Twelve hour head start.
They could be in Moscow by now.

07:00.962 --> 07:02.797
I don't think so.

07:02.881 --> 07:04.132
When I talked to her yesterday,

07:04.215 --> 07:05.550
she was concerned about
her friend, Max.

07:05.634 --> 07:07.802
As far as she could tell,
no one was looking for him.

07:07.886 --> 07:09.220
Oh, Christ.

07:09.304 --> 07:11.264
She'd gone to Yevgeny about it.

07:11.348 --> 07:12.557
What?

07:12.641 --> 07:14.893
Russians have better contacts
in the tribal areas.

07:14.976 --> 07:16.936
She thought she could
take advantage of that.

07:17.020 --> 07:20.440
And I'm just
hearing about it now?

07:21.650 --> 07:23.693
It's why I sent her home.

07:23.777 --> 07:24.569
I'm turning this over
to the FBI,

07:24.653 --> 07:26.488
which I would
have done yesterday

07:26.571 --> 07:27.489
if you hadn't
talked me out of it.

07:27.572 --> 07:30.700
Do what you have to.
Just get her back.

07:30.784 --> 07:33.578
♪ tense music ♪

07:33.662 --> 07:36.956
[woman on radio]
speaking Russian

07:44.422 --> 07:47.342
He turned himself in.

07:47.425 --> 07:50.345
Haqqani did.

07:50.428 --> 07:52.347
"The mastermind
behind the downing

07:52.430 --> 07:55.225
of the presidents' helicopter."

07:55.308 --> 07:57.352
That's what
they're calling him.

07:57.435 --> 08:00.188
You don't believe it?

08:01.356 --> 08:03.149
Do you?

08:04.651 --> 08:07.779
He is capable.

08:07.862 --> 08:09.781
Yeah, if what you mean
is he doesn't mind

08:09.864 --> 08:10.782
seeing America hurt.

08:13.743 --> 08:16.287
But how'd he get the intel?

08:16.371 --> 08:17.831
How'd he know
the presidents' helicopter

08:17.914 --> 08:21.584
would be in that exact place
at that exact time?

08:23.169 --> 08:25.380
I don't know.

08:25.463 --> 08:27.966
See, I do.

08:28.049 --> 08:31.886
Or at least I know what certain
people in the CIA think.

08:33.179 --> 08:36.099
An American traitor, me,

08:36.182 --> 08:38.560
passed the intel
to a Russian handler, you,

08:38.643 --> 08:41.438
who in turn alerted Haqqani.

08:44.232 --> 08:46.109
They actually believe that?

08:46.192 --> 08:49.404
Some do.

08:51.031 --> 08:53.283
If they weren't sure before,
they will be now.

08:54.075 --> 08:57.871
Since we're
out here together.

09:03.209 --> 09:04.961
Ironic.

09:05.045 --> 09:07.130
Yeah.

09:07.213 --> 09:10.925
♪ uneasy music ♪

09:11.009 --> 09:16.347
♪♪♪

09:24.189 --> 09:27.275
speaking Pashto

09:34.365 --> 09:35.700
What's going on?

09:39.204 --> 09:41.456
Stay here.

09:48.922 --> 09:51.132
speaking Pashto

09:54.552 --> 09:57.722
[inaudible dialogue]

10:08.608 --> 10:10.902
speaking Pashto

10:16.908 --> 10:18.785
We okay?

10:18.868 --> 10:21.871
Yeah, they're my guys.

10:21.955 --> 10:23.706
They have a line on Max.

10:36.970 --> 10:39.889
♪ uneasy music ♪

10:39.973 --> 10:45.103
♪♪♪

10:56.447 --> 10:58.741
[sheep bleating]

11:07.458 --> 11:10.837
[indistinct chatter]

11:18.261 --> 11:20.346
speaking Pashto

11:25.143 --> 11:27.896
[sighs]

11:27.979 --> 11:31.065
♪ light uneasy music ♪

11:31.149 --> 11:36.196
♪♪♪

11:41.910 --> 11:43.995
[engine sputtering]

12:11.356 --> 12:14.442
[animal bleats]

12:17.904 --> 12:20.907
♪ light music ♪

12:20.990 --> 12:23.201
♪♪♪

12:23.284 --> 12:26.996
[indistinct chatter]

12:40.843 --> 12:43.221
[breathes raggedly]

12:44.013 --> 12:45.932
[man] Weapons free.
Ten seconds to impact.

12:48.768 --> 12:53.856
♪♪♪

13:34.647 --> 13:37.483
You really should stay
in the car.

13:37.567 --> 13:39.068
‐ Quit fucking with me.
‐ What?

13:39.152 --> 13:40.153
Quit fucking with me!

13:40.236 --> 13:42.864
I'm not.

13:42.947 --> 13:45.616
What, so it's just
a coincidence we end up here?

13:45.700 --> 13:46.701
Wait, you came to me for help.
You don't get to complain.

13:46.784 --> 13:49.370
About this, yeah, yeah, I do.
[scoffs]

13:49.454 --> 13:52.373
[breathes deeply]

13:52.457 --> 13:54.333
You want to use my contacts,
right?

13:54.417 --> 13:56.544
Where do you think
they come from, huh?

13:56.627 --> 13:58.212
It's places like this.

13:58.296 --> 14:02.091
Every time America comes in
and bombs a bunch of civilians,

14:02.175 --> 14:04.385
it's an opportunity for us.

14:04.469 --> 14:07.055
We come in,
we rebuild the mosque,

14:07.138 --> 14:09.849
we help people
get their lives back together.

14:09.932 --> 14:14.479
We make friends.
That's how it works.

14:14.562 --> 14:16.397
So is it a coincidence
we're here?

14:16.481 --> 14:20.359
No, but it doesn't mean
I'm fucking with you.

14:21.527 --> 14:23.780
Okay?

14:29.452 --> 14:31.662
What did the imam say?

14:31.746 --> 14:34.582
He knows where Max is.

14:34.665 --> 14:36.793
It's not far.

14:43.508 --> 14:46.094
It's important
we get this right,

14:46.177 --> 14:48.763
or we'll be looking
at a level of Taliban violence

14:48.846 --> 14:51.432
we haven't seen
in a dozen years.

14:51.516 --> 14:53.976
Haqqani's not just some leader.

14:54.060 --> 14:56.145
He is the living, breathing
avatar of his people,

14:56.229 --> 14:58.815
and I do not get the feeling
G'ulom appreciates that,

14:58.898 --> 15:01.275
or more likely,
he does appreciate it

15:01.359 --> 15:02.443
and he wants to snuff it out.

15:02.527 --> 15:04.695
What are you pushing exactly?

15:04.779 --> 15:06.280
Rule of law.

15:06.364 --> 15:09.033
Some semblance
of a fair trial.

15:10.159 --> 15:11.786
We've spent hundreds
of millions of dollars

15:11.869 --> 15:14.622
setting up
a judicial system here.

15:14.705 --> 15:16.415
Let's make it work for once.

15:16.499 --> 15:17.708
We got word that G'ulom

15:17.792 --> 15:20.461
has already appointed
the three‐judge panel.

15:20.545 --> 15:22.004
Right, which in theory

15:22.088 --> 15:25.049
means he's following
the constitution.

15:25.133 --> 15:27.927
In practice though, they're
gonna do what G'ulom wants.

15:28.010 --> 15:29.929
I don't know what could be
done, if anything,

15:30.012 --> 15:31.764
but I do know the lead judge

15:31.848 --> 15:33.349
from these women's leadership
events at the embassy,

15:33.432 --> 15:36.144
Haziq Qadir.

15:36.227 --> 15:38.020
She's fair, independent.

15:38.104 --> 15:40.481
Obviously that has limits.

15:40.565 --> 15:43.401
If there's a way into this,
it's probably her.

15:43.484 --> 15:45.319
Will this judge be open
to a meeting?

15:45.403 --> 15:48.239
I can ask.

15:48.322 --> 15:50.533
[clears throat]
Mr. President.

15:50.616 --> 15:51.951
I was looking for you.

15:52.034 --> 15:55.121
C‐can we pick this up later?

15:55.204 --> 15:57.540
Oh, no, no.
No, no, please.

15:57.623 --> 15:59.792
Carry on.

15:59.876 --> 16:01.252
I'll just listen in.

16:03.504 --> 16:06.174
Saul, you were
saying something

16:06.257 --> 16:09.886
about contacting a judge?

16:09.969 --> 16:11.679
Yes, sir, I was.

16:11.762 --> 16:13.431
Well, what about?

16:13.514 --> 16:17.268
[Saul] Submitting evidence
on Haqqani's behalf.

16:19.353 --> 16:21.022
The fact is, sir,
we're in possession

16:21.105 --> 16:23.941
of a signals intercept that all
but proves Haqqani's innocence.

16:24.025 --> 16:27.653
In it, he's dressing down
his son, Jalal,

16:27.737 --> 16:30.114
for an attack on a government
outpost in Sang‐e‐Masha.

16:30.198 --> 16:33.868
He also goes on at length
about the need for peace

16:33.951 --> 16:37.038
and insists that
any further violence

16:37.121 --> 16:39.832
be stopped immediately,
which it was.

16:39.916 --> 16:40.750
I can testify
to Haqqani's mindset

16:40.833 --> 16:43.044
based on my meetings with him,

16:43.127 --> 16:44.921
but it will have
nowhere near the impact

16:45.004 --> 16:47.590
of hearing Haqqani
in his own words,

16:47.673 --> 16:50.593
in his own voice
foreswearing violence.

16:50.676 --> 16:53.429
The problem is this.

16:53.512 --> 16:56.724
Currently the intercept
is highly classified.

16:56.807 --> 17:00.019
One of the things I wanted
to discuss with this room

17:00.102 --> 17:01.729
is how we undo that.

17:01.812 --> 17:04.023
May I say something?

17:04.106 --> 17:05.233
Because I see
another problem.

17:05.316 --> 17:08.069
And forgive me if you've
already discussed this.

17:08.152 --> 17:10.112
I was a little late
to the party as you know.

17:10.196 --> 17:15.576
Tomorrow, the body
of President Ralph Warner

17:15.660 --> 17:16.869
will arrive
at Dover Air Force Base.

17:16.953 --> 17:19.330
I will be there to receive it

17:19.413 --> 17:23.167
right next to the president's
grieving widow.

17:23.251 --> 17:27.046
And here's what people
will be asking:

17:27.129 --> 17:32.218
What are we doing to avenge
her murdered husband?

17:34.178 --> 17:37.598
That's what Americans
everywhere will be asking,

17:37.682 --> 17:39.183
everywhere but here
in this room,

17:39.267 --> 17:40.101
where for some reason
the question is:

17:40.184 --> 17:42.770
How do we help
the man who murdered him?

17:42.853 --> 17:45.523
‐ Mr. President‐‐
‐ [Hayes] No!

17:45.606 --> 17:48.651
You will not expose
our classified materials.

17:48.734 --> 17:52.113
You will not expose
our sources and methods.

17:52.196 --> 17:54.699
Didn't think I knew that term,
did you, Saul?

17:54.782 --> 17:57.785
Get me the goddamn action plan

17:57.868 --> 17:59.245
I asked for two days ago.

18:02.039 --> 18:04.709
[door opens, slams]

18:04.792 --> 18:07.628
♪ uneasy music ♪

18:07.712 --> 18:08.629
♪♪♪

18:08.713 --> 18:10.631
[sighs]

18:10.715 --> 18:12.633
[birds chirping]

18:12.717 --> 18:18.014
♪♪♪

18:25.062 --> 18:29.150
It was you, wasn't it?

18:29.233 --> 18:31.819
The airstrike
on the village.

18:33.279 --> 18:36.532
You were Kabul's
chief of station then.

18:36.616 --> 18:38.576
You must have signed off.

18:41.912 --> 18:43.623
I didn't know.

18:43.706 --> 18:47.752
I mean, I...

18:47.835 --> 18:51.339
I didn't put it together.

18:51.422 --> 18:53.424
I didn't.

18:58.471 --> 19:01.390
♪ light music ♪

19:01.474 --> 19:06.604
♪♪♪

19:08.022 --> 19:12.568
You know who the target was?

19:12.652 --> 19:14.654
Haqqani.

19:17.531 --> 19:20.284
[sighs]
He was supposed to be there.

19:20.368 --> 19:21.869
He wasn't.

19:21.952 --> 19:25.289
A wedding party was.

19:27.875 --> 19:30.878
Including
a half dozen children.

19:34.924 --> 19:37.677
It changed everything.

19:40.763 --> 19:43.057
You left the CIA.

19:43.140 --> 19:44.934
No, not at first.

19:45.017 --> 19:47.895
What I did first was double
down on getting Haqqani.

19:47.978 --> 19:51.899
That's‐that's how I thought
I could make things right.

19:51.982 --> 19:54.902
Then more people died.

19:54.985 --> 19:59.490
Cracks began to appear
in my resolve.

20:02.034 --> 20:04.328
And that is when
I left the CIA.

20:10.000 --> 20:11.293
[sighs]

20:16.132 --> 20:18.426
Did you really not know
about the village,

20:18.509 --> 20:21.429
that I was the one
who pulled the trigger?

20:21.512 --> 20:24.473
‐ I said.
‐ Say it again.

20:24.557 --> 20:25.933
Because to be honest,

20:26.016 --> 20:28.269
I'm not quite sure
what you're doing here.

20:28.352 --> 20:31.689
I'm trying to find your friend.

20:31.772 --> 20:37.111
♪♪♪

20:43.242 --> 20:45.119
[animal bleats]

20:45.202 --> 20:48.205
♪ tense music ♪

20:48.289 --> 20:53.335
♪♪♪

20:56.547 --> 20:59.717
[indistinct chatter]

21:14.899 --> 21:15.566
speaking Pashto

21:24.492 --> 21:26.827
speaking Pashto

21:26.911 --> 21:29.038
We're here to pick up
the American.

21:29.121 --> 21:30.998
No, no, the American
is not for sale.

21:31.081 --> 21:32.583
Well, we were just
with Maulawi Saib,

21:32.666 --> 21:34.668
and he said
everything was arranged.

21:34.752 --> 21:36.337
With respect,
Maulawi Saib is mistaken.

21:36.420 --> 21:38.714
‐ You may visit the American.
‐ No.

21:38.798 --> 21:40.674
‐ Not take him.
‐ Is he inside?

21:40.758 --> 21:43.010
Wait, wait, wait.
Business.

21:43.093 --> 21:44.595
The imam said it's $2,000

21:44.678 --> 21:47.056
for us to take
the American with us.

21:47.139 --> 21:49.683
Now, a visit
is worth much less.

21:50.559 --> 21:53.145
Ah, look at me, look at me.
I've got more money here.

21:53.229 --> 21:56.023
[Yevgeny]
Do you want the rest?

21:59.360 --> 22:01.779
‐ Carrie.
‐ [Carrie] Oh, my God.

22:01.862 --> 22:03.239
Are you okay?

22:03.322 --> 22:06.116
Uh, yeah, yeah.
[groaning] I'm fine.

22:06.200 --> 22:08.911
‐ Yeah.
‐ Let me see.

22:08.994 --> 22:09.870
[winces]

22:09.954 --> 22:12.498
I had it.

22:12.581 --> 22:14.542
The black box.

22:14.625 --> 22:18.712
He sold it to some other guy,
this guy Firooz.

22:18.796 --> 22:22.216
All my other stuff,
he sold it to someone.

22:22.299 --> 22:26.178
They took it somewhere,
it was Koa or Kowa‐‐

22:26.262 --> 22:27.555
‐ Kohat.
‐ Yeah.

22:27.638 --> 22:29.849
Yeah, we passed the cutoff
on the way here.

22:29.932 --> 22:31.851
[groans]
I don't know what's on it.

22:31.934 --> 22:33.018
That's okay.

22:33.102 --> 22:34.186
I just didn't want him to know
how important it was.

22:34.270 --> 22:37.231
Max, listen to me,
you did good.

22:37.314 --> 22:39.733
You did good.

22:39.817 --> 22:41.777
But I'm worried
about your back.

22:41.861 --> 22:43.279
Yeah, that fucker shot me.

22:43.362 --> 22:46.448
I think the bullet's
still in there.

22:46.532 --> 22:48.576
What have they given you
for infection?

22:48.659 --> 22:49.952
Nothing.

22:54.832 --> 22:56.792
‐ Where‐where are you going?
‐ Back to the truck.

22:56.876 --> 22:58.878
They must have something.
Antibiotics.

22:58.961 --> 22:59.962
No, no, you‐you can't.

23:00.045 --> 23:01.505
Carrie,
we don't have much time.

23:01.589 --> 23:03.799
What do you mean?

23:03.883 --> 23:04.925
Max?

23:05.009 --> 23:06.927
[engines rev]

23:09.138 --> 23:12.099
speaking Pashto

23:21.025 --> 23:23.277
[Yevgeny]
This isn't right.

23:23.360 --> 23:27.531
You hear me?
This isn't right.

23:30.075 --> 23:32.620
No.
No.

23:32.703 --> 23:33.954
What do you think you're doing?

23:34.038 --> 23:36.832
Carrie.

23:36.916 --> 23:37.708
[Max groans]

23:37.791 --> 23:41.086
[Carrie]
Where are you taking him?

23:41.170 --> 23:43.005
I'll find you, Max.

23:43.088 --> 23:43.964
Do you hear me?
I will find you.

23:44.048 --> 23:48.636
[Max groaning softly]

23:48.719 --> 23:50.304
[Yevgeny]
Where are they taking him?

23:50.387 --> 23:51.639
Hey, look over here, where?
Turn around, look.

23:51.722 --> 23:54.224
What's the name of the man
you gave the key to?

23:54.308 --> 23:55.809
[Barlas] I don't know him.

23:55.893 --> 23:56.810
[Yevgeny] What do you mean,
you don't know him?

23:56.894 --> 23:58.938
‐ I honestly don't‐‐
‐ Turn around, look.

23:59.021 --> 23:59.897
There's three cars here
full of Talibs.

23:59.980 --> 24:01.982
‐ I don't know.
‐ Where are they going?

24:02.066 --> 24:03.484
[Barlas] In the hills
somewhere, I tell you‐‐

24:03.567 --> 24:05.027
[Yevgeny] Hill where?
Where are they going?

24:05.110 --> 24:06.111
[Barlas]
Honestly, I don't know.

24:06.195 --> 24:08.364
Tell me where they're taking
him, you motherfucker!

24:08.447 --> 24:09.239
speaking Pashto

24:09.323 --> 24:12.576
I will take care of this.

24:15.245 --> 24:17.122
[breathing heavily]

24:17.206 --> 24:20.167
♪ tense music ♪

24:20.250 --> 24:25.506
♪♪♪

24:26.090 --> 24:27.424
Tell me where
they are going.

24:27.508 --> 24:30.219
Tell me and you get
the rest of this.

24:30.302 --> 24:32.680
Huh?

24:32.763 --> 24:34.390
Or otherwise,
we have a problem.

24:34.473 --> 24:37.559
[engine roaring]

24:44.775 --> 24:45.651
[Hayes] Nine months in office.

24:45.734 --> 24:48.195
Not the shortest
presidential term ever.

24:48.278 --> 24:49.571
That would be
William Henry Harrison,

24:49.655 --> 24:51.448
also responsible
for his own demise.

24:51.532 --> 24:56.954
You, on the other hand,
are a survivor.

24:57.037 --> 24:58.747
The chief of staff
for a president

24:58.831 --> 25:01.750
who's nearly assassinated
then resigns.

25:01.834 --> 25:03.877
Chief of staff
for her successor.

25:03.961 --> 25:06.714
He's coming home
in a body bag.

25:06.797 --> 25:08.132
Sir, if you want
my resignation‐‐

25:08.215 --> 25:11.093
Did I say that?

25:11.176 --> 25:15.014
What I want is your loyalty.

25:15.097 --> 25:17.850
That is not the vibe I get when
I walk into the situation room.

25:17.933 --> 25:19.643
You're huddled there
behind my back.

25:22.354 --> 25:24.273
Well?

25:24.356 --> 25:26.066
Clearly, I need guidelines,

25:26.150 --> 25:27.735
which meetings
you want to attend and‐‐

25:27.818 --> 25:29.570
Bullshit, that wasn't
a meeting, it was a cabal,

25:29.653 --> 25:31.530
led by the same man
who told the president

25:31.613 --> 25:35.576
it was safe
to trust a terrorist.

25:35.659 --> 25:38.662
Okay.
Say it was.

25:38.746 --> 25:40.414
Then the last thing you want
is for them to be there

25:40.497 --> 25:42.833
and neither of us
is in the room,

25:42.916 --> 25:45.169
because then we're outside
the information flow

25:45.252 --> 25:48.338
and then you've got a problem.

25:48.422 --> 25:49.048
Fine.

25:49.131 --> 25:51.341
‐ Sir?
‐ Fine.

25:51.425 --> 25:54.094
We'll leave you there for now.

25:54.178 --> 25:56.597
In the information flow.
Excuse me.

25:56.680 --> 25:58.849
[whispered conversations]

26:01.727 --> 26:03.479
Doris.

26:03.562 --> 26:05.939
I'm so sorry.

26:06.023 --> 26:08.776
We all are.
He was a good man.

26:08.859 --> 26:10.069
Don't.

26:10.152 --> 26:11.028
You drop a bomb on him

26:11.111 --> 26:14.073
and then fly
an empty casket 7,500 miles

26:14.156 --> 26:16.116
so you can look, what,
presidential?

26:16.200 --> 26:17.493
That's why we're here.

26:17.576 --> 26:21.080
And don't tell me
how sorry you are.

26:21.163 --> 26:24.124
♪ somber music ♪

26:24.208 --> 26:26.335
♪♪♪

26:26.418 --> 26:28.128
[exhales deeply]

26:28.212 --> 26:33.258
♪♪♪

26:35.427 --> 26:36.678
You invited him?

26:36.762 --> 26:38.806
He asked to come
to pay his respects.

26:38.889 --> 26:41.183
Respects.
To my husband.

26:41.266 --> 26:43.644
When that man spent the last
six months attacking him.

26:43.727 --> 26:46.897
Doris, let go of me, please.

26:53.070 --> 26:58.408
♪♪♪

27:06.250 --> 27:08.627
Mr. President.

27:08.710 --> 27:11.046
Mr. President, it's good
to meet you in person.

27:11.130 --> 27:14.133
Finally.

27:45.205 --> 27:47.666
National Security Advisor.

27:47.749 --> 27:50.168
I finally hear from you.

27:50.252 --> 27:51.837
Good to see you again.

27:51.920 --> 27:54.756
I hope so.

28:04.474 --> 28:06.560
[door closes]

28:09.146 --> 28:11.398
Saul.

28:12.649 --> 28:14.234
I was under the impression

28:14.318 --> 28:16.236
we'd have the chance
to speak alone.

28:16.320 --> 28:19.156
I have no secrets
from Tasneem.

28:19.573 --> 28:22.451
I understand.

28:22.534 --> 28:24.912
The fact is
we've been at odds lately.

28:24.995 --> 28:27.581
So you go behind my back again.

28:28.373 --> 28:30.334
I ask an old friend
for advice.

28:30.417 --> 28:35.255
Anything you want to say,
you can say to us both.

28:35.339 --> 28:37.674
[Bunny] Please.

28:44.890 --> 28:49.645
Haissam Haqqani
is now in custody in Kabul.

28:49.728 --> 28:52.981
General G'ulom
wants a firing squad.

28:53.065 --> 28:54.900
There will be a trial first.

28:54.983 --> 28:56.568
[Saul]
Show trial at best.

28:56.652 --> 28:58.153
Unless we intervene.

28:58.236 --> 28:59.613
‐ We?
‐ [Saul] Yes.

28:59.696 --> 29:02.491
'Cause we know the truth,
the three of us.

29:02.574 --> 29:04.785
Haissam Haqqani
didn't shoot down

29:04.868 --> 29:07.704
the presidents' helicopter,
quite the opposite.

29:07.788 --> 29:10.749
He was looking forward
to meeting the men on board.

29:12.042 --> 29:15.295
He wanted to stop
the fighting.

29:15.379 --> 29:17.965
I have signals intercepts
to prove it.

29:18.048 --> 29:19.257
So make them public.

29:19.341 --> 29:21.009
I've been told
in no uncertain terms I can't.

29:21.093 --> 29:23.637
Or maybe you don't
actually have them.

29:25.973 --> 29:29.017
Your father and I
have an agreement.

29:29.101 --> 29:31.478
Whatever we say out there,

29:31.561 --> 29:34.106
here in this room
we tell the truth.

29:34.189 --> 29:36.817
You wanna be here,
then you do that too.

29:36.900 --> 29:38.860
You know I have them.

29:44.783 --> 29:47.577
You worked with Haqqani
for decades.

29:47.661 --> 29:50.330
You knew his mind had changed.

29:50.414 --> 29:51.873
He wanted peace.

29:51.957 --> 29:53.125
What do you want?

29:53.834 --> 29:58.338
Anything that might
slow the trial.

29:58.422 --> 30:00.799
Anything that might
prevent the violence

30:00.882 --> 30:02.926
that would follow
his execution.

30:03.010 --> 30:04.344
Oh.

30:04.428 --> 30:07.014
You want us to compromise
our sources.

30:07.097 --> 30:09.099
Yes.

30:09.182 --> 30:11.309
If that's what it takes.

30:13.353 --> 30:15.939
Haqqani's outlived
his usefulness to you.

30:16.023 --> 30:19.443
You think you don't care
if he dies.

30:19.526 --> 30:21.319
I'm telling you,
you should.

30:23.238 --> 30:24.698
When those helicopters
went down,

30:24.781 --> 30:27.367
two things changed
in my country.

30:27.451 --> 30:30.370
An inexperienced president
came to power.

30:30.454 --> 30:32.748
The American people
were wounded,

30:32.831 --> 30:35.459
demanding action.

30:35.542 --> 30:38.378
We know what happens next.
We've been here before.

30:39.629 --> 30:42.299
How does a weak president
show he's strong?

30:44.051 --> 30:46.845
He goes to war.

30:46.928 --> 30:49.056
And that's
what will happen again

30:49.139 --> 30:53.101
unless sensible people can
put aside their differences.

30:53.810 --> 30:55.228
You want us to work together?

30:55.312 --> 30:57.397
Yes.

30:57.481 --> 30:58.982
Like '79,

30:59.066 --> 31:01.651
when the Soviets invaded
Afghanistan.

31:01.735 --> 31:04.321
[Bunny] We were friends then.

31:05.655 --> 31:09.076
And after 9/11,
when you needed us,

31:09.159 --> 31:11.161
friends again.

31:11.244 --> 31:14.456
In between,
not such good friends.

31:14.539 --> 31:15.791
You forget us.

31:15.874 --> 31:17.626
No, not forget.

31:17.709 --> 31:19.961
You'd lecture, belittle,

31:20.045 --> 31:23.131
withhold aid,
violate our borders,

31:23.215 --> 31:26.551
send your drones
to murder our citizens.

31:28.011 --> 31:30.097
Until you need our help,

31:30.180 --> 31:32.140
and then here you are

31:32.224 --> 31:35.644
in my living room
saying we're friends again.

31:36.853 --> 31:39.981
I thought you said
in here we tell the truth.

31:43.360 --> 31:45.445
If war starts in Afghanistan‐‐

31:45.529 --> 31:48.240
You'll be burned, not us.

31:49.491 --> 31:52.369
We'll be hurt, yes.

31:52.452 --> 31:54.996
But we're 7,000 miles away.

31:55.539 --> 31:58.375
You live here.

32:00.043 --> 32:02.838
The war will land on you.

32:13.557 --> 32:17.644
[birds chirping]

32:25.235 --> 32:27.279
[sighs]

32:27.362 --> 32:29.948
Back to the airport.

32:30.031 --> 32:31.491
Please.

32:37.330 --> 32:38.123
I'll help you.

32:39.416 --> 32:41.042
Why?

32:41.126 --> 32:45.463
I don't want to watch
the world burn.

32:52.053 --> 32:53.263
‐ [engine starts]
‐ [sighs]

32:56.099 --> 32:59.019
♪ uneasy music ♪

32:59.102 --> 33:04.232
♪♪♪

33:30.508 --> 33:33.178
[Carrie] Yeah, they've put
guards out front.

33:35.055 --> 33:36.723
It must be Max.

33:36.806 --> 33:39.351
They look like teenagers.

33:39.434 --> 33:42.103
What, are we going
to surprise them?

33:42.187 --> 33:44.731
Grab your friend, hmm?

33:44.814 --> 33:45.565
‐ The three of us.
‐ [Carrie] Four.

33:45.649 --> 33:47.901
I can handle myself.

33:47.984 --> 33:49.903
I'm not starting
a war with the Taliban.

33:49.986 --> 33:51.279
[birds chirping]

33:51.363 --> 33:52.489
[Yevgeny sighs]

33:52.572 --> 33:54.532
♪ tense music ♪

33:54.616 --> 34:00.705
♪♪♪

34:07.545 --> 34:08.588
Who are you calling?

34:08.672 --> 34:10.298
Saul Berenson.

34:10.382 --> 34:13.593
‐ You think that's a good idea?
‐ Well, it's an idea.

34:13.677 --> 34:15.553
He can order up
an extraction team.

34:15.637 --> 34:17.430
[sighs]

34:17.514 --> 34:22.143
♪♪♪

34:22.227 --> 34:24.145
[line ringing]

34:28.024 --> 34:29.943
[Saul] Saul Berenson.
Leave a message.

34:30.026 --> 34:31.778
‐ [sighs]
‐ [phone beeps]

34:37.367 --> 34:40.787
[phone beeps]

34:40.870 --> 34:42.622
[line ringing]

34:42.706 --> 34:44.958
‐ [phone rings]
‐ Jenna Bragg.

34:45.709 --> 34:48.128
It's Carrie.

34:48.211 --> 34:51.172
‐ I need your help.
‐ Are you kidding?

34:51.256 --> 34:53.550
You ditched me at the airport,
made me look like an idiot.

34:53.633 --> 34:54.467
You're right, I'm sorry.

34:54.551 --> 34:56.261
Now can you
just listen please?

34:56.344 --> 34:59.055
[whispered]
It's Carrie Mathison.

34:59.139 --> 35:01.308
What are you doing, Carrie?

35:01.391 --> 35:02.684
I found Max.

35:02.767 --> 35:04.019
[door closes]

35:04.102 --> 35:05.562
Who are you with?

35:05.645 --> 35:06.980
He's at an isolated farm,

35:07.063 --> 35:09.608
seven miles across
the Pakistan border.

35:09.691 --> 35:10.775
Okay, write this down,

35:10.859 --> 35:14.654
32, 97, 00 north,

35:14.738 --> 35:18.241
70, 27, 76 east.

35:18.325 --> 35:19.367
He's been shot,
he's critical,

35:19.451 --> 35:21.703
being held by seven Taliban,
mostly teenagers,

35:21.786 --> 35:24.164
armed only with rifles.

35:24.247 --> 35:26.416
Get a drone overhead.
It'll confirm.

35:30.128 --> 35:32.589
‐ Tell me you got that.
‐ Yeah.

35:32.672 --> 35:33.965
Then pass it
to Special Operations,

35:34.049 --> 35:35.634
get a rescue mission going.

35:35.717 --> 35:36.760
He's close to the border,
lightly guarded.

35:36.843 --> 35:39.846
God knows for how long.
Will you talk to Special Ops?

35:39.929 --> 35:42.390
Do you have any idea
the trouble you're in?

35:42.474 --> 35:44.434
Mike, will you talk to them?

35:46.770 --> 35:48.271
Yes.

35:48.355 --> 35:49.522
Thank you.

35:49.606 --> 35:50.273
[Mike] Your case is now
with the FBI.

35:50.357 --> 35:51.858
You're officially a fugitive.

35:51.941 --> 35:54.986
You know what that means?

35:55.070 --> 35:58.114
Carrie?

36:02.535 --> 36:05.246
An unscheduled summit.

36:05.330 --> 36:08.625
That's what they're calling it.

36:08.708 --> 36:11.878
They're wondering
what we'll do.

36:13.296 --> 36:15.215
We will do what we agreed.

36:15.298 --> 36:19.052
The Taliban declared war,
we give them war.

36:19.135 --> 36:20.720
Yes.

36:20.804 --> 36:24.057
Except we've been
giving them war for 18 years.

36:24.140 --> 36:26.059
Bullshit.

36:26.142 --> 36:28.228
You didn't fight
for 18 years.

36:28.311 --> 36:30.897
You fought for eight weeks.

36:30.980 --> 36:34.776
You invaded Afghanistan
with 12 men and airpower,

36:34.859 --> 36:36.820
bombed the Taliban to shit,

36:36.903 --> 36:41.032
and in days they were
lining up to surrender.

36:41.116 --> 36:43.576
They were making deals,

36:43.660 --> 36:45.995
shaving their beards.

36:46.079 --> 36:48.581
You'd won.

36:48.665 --> 36:50.500
Then you gave up

36:50.583 --> 36:52.919
and left for Iraq.

36:54.129 --> 36:56.548
Fight like you did then,

36:56.631 --> 36:58.425
you will win again.

36:58.508 --> 37:00.427
You.

37:00.510 --> 37:05.473
Once Haqqani's gone,
the Taliban will be leaderless.

37:05.557 --> 37:10.145
Now is the time to act.

37:11.146 --> 37:13.815
When Haqqani's gone.

37:13.898 --> 37:16.526
Which will be very, very soon.

37:16.609 --> 37:19.279
Maybe.

37:19.362 --> 37:24.075
I, uh, stumbled into a meeting,
my advisors‐‐

37:24.159 --> 37:25.618
Fuck your advisors.

37:25.702 --> 37:28.872
They're the same men who
sent Warner into the Korengal,

37:28.955 --> 37:31.583
waving the white flag.

37:31.666 --> 37:33.293
Believe me, I know,
and now they're unhappy

37:33.376 --> 37:37.130
about this trial
you've got going in Kabul.

37:37.213 --> 37:39.716
How unhappy?

37:39.799 --> 37:43.136
Very.

37:43.219 --> 37:46.222
♪ uneasy music ♪

37:46.306 --> 37:51.352
♪♪♪

38:13.500 --> 38:14.959
[intercom buzzes]

38:15.043 --> 38:17.420
[door beeps, buzzes]

38:30.475 --> 38:32.227
Saul Berenson.

38:32.310 --> 38:34.229
Tasneem Qureishi.

38:37.690 --> 38:39.192
We appreciate
you meeting with us,

38:39.275 --> 38:40.860
‐Your Honor.
‐Mm.

38:44.656 --> 38:48.701
I told your ambassador
this is highly irregular.

38:48.785 --> 38:50.119
She insisted.

38:50.203 --> 38:52.038
We're not trying
to compromise you.

38:52.121 --> 38:53.998
Then what do you want?

38:56.668 --> 39:01.506
Your Honor, Haqqani is not
the man you think.

39:01.589 --> 39:03.132
He changed.
He wanted peace.

39:03.216 --> 39:06.928
He agreed to a ceasefire.

39:07.011 --> 39:08.847
He was about to meet
with my president

39:08.930 --> 39:10.223
to sign an agreement.

39:10.306 --> 39:12.559
He didn't kill him
or order his death.

39:12.642 --> 39:14.561
Haqqani's welcome to say that.

39:14.644 --> 39:18.022
And no one would listen.

39:18.106 --> 39:21.359
Which is why we're here.

39:21.442 --> 39:24.737
I have classified intelligence
that proves it.

39:25.738 --> 39:28.449
‐ You do?
‐ We both do.

39:30.660 --> 39:32.620
Then offer it as evidence.

39:32.704 --> 39:34.581
Unfortunately,
that's not possible.

39:36.833 --> 39:40.086
Then stand up in court and
repeat what you just told me.

39:40.169 --> 39:42.255
I'm sorry, we can't.

39:42.338 --> 39:45.008
Can you tell me who did
shoot down the helicopters?

39:45.091 --> 39:47.594
We have teams in the field
looking for evidence.

39:47.677 --> 39:50.597
Looking?

39:50.680 --> 39:53.474
This is really inappropriate.

39:53.558 --> 39:55.768
I'm going to have
to ask you to leave.

39:55.852 --> 39:57.854
Your Honor,

39:57.937 --> 40:01.399
I know there's a lot
of pressure on you.

40:01.482 --> 40:03.234
What is that supposed to mean?

40:03.318 --> 40:06.905
It's no secret,
people want Haqqani dead.

40:08.031 --> 40:09.449
Don't you dare.

40:09.532 --> 40:12.785
Don't you dare impugn me
when you're unwilling

40:12.869 --> 40:16.247
to stand up and say
what you claim is the truth.

40:16.331 --> 40:18.416
You sneak here
in the middle of the night,

40:18.499 --> 40:20.126
offering no evidence.

40:20.209 --> 40:21.961
"Just trust me."

40:22.045 --> 40:23.838
Haissam Haqqani has changed.

40:23.922 --> 40:26.549
He's now Mahatma Gandhi.

40:26.633 --> 40:28.927
I should never
have agreed to this.

40:29.010 --> 40:34.015
♪ tense music ♪

40:34.098 --> 40:36.726
What do you think
you're doing?

40:39.437 --> 40:42.482
You want evidence?
Here.

40:42.565 --> 40:44.442
This happened eight days ago.

40:44.525 --> 40:46.319
Haqqani was supposed
to be in that car.

40:46.402 --> 40:48.947
[Tasneem] I heard
he wanted to make peace.

40:49.030 --> 40:50.323
I wanted to stop him.

40:50.406 --> 40:53.701
So I put an RPG
through his windshield.

40:55.203 --> 40:57.497
It didn't stop him.

40:57.580 --> 40:58.498
He was still determined
to make peace.

40:58.581 --> 41:01.626
I know he didn't kill
the presidents.

41:01.709 --> 41:06.756
♪♪♪

41:07.924 --> 41:09.926
What do you want?

41:10.009 --> 41:11.135
Time.

41:11.219 --> 41:13.596
[Saul]
Just that.

41:18.393 --> 41:20.269
I'll open the trial
tomorrow as scheduled

41:20.353 --> 41:23.940
and then order a continuance,

41:24.023 --> 41:26.859
but I don't know
how much time I can give you.

41:26.943 --> 41:29.612
A week maybe.
No more.

41:33.408 --> 41:36.369
Fine.
Thank you.

41:38.663 --> 41:41.666
♪ tense music ♪

41:41.749 --> 41:46.796
♪♪♪

42:06.649 --> 42:08.276
‐ What's happening?
‐ Someone's coming.

42:08.359 --> 42:10.403
Special Ops?

42:26.711 --> 42:29.922
[Carrie] Oh, shit.

42:30.006 --> 42:32.133
It's Jalal Haqqani.

42:49.067 --> 42:52.111
[groaning softly]

43:10.671 --> 43:14.634
They told me you were
at the helicopters.

43:14.717 --> 43:15.968
Who shot them down?

43:16.052 --> 43:19.722
Did you see?

43:19.806 --> 43:22.892
[breathing heavily]

43:25.103 --> 43:28.898
What helicopters?

43:32.276 --> 43:35.488
[groans, breathing heavily]

43:49.585 --> 43:50.670
It's Jalal Haqqani.
I'm sure of it.

43:50.753 --> 43:53.673
G'ulom has his father,
he has Max.

43:53.756 --> 43:55.049
This is a bad situation.

43:55.133 --> 43:57.718
Where the hell
is the extraction team?

43:57.802 --> 44:00.179
‐ Mike, are you listening?
‐ Yeah.

44:00.263 --> 44:02.390
‐ Did you call them even?
‐ Yes.

44:02.473 --> 44:03.808
What's taking them so long?

44:03.891 --> 44:04.684
What do you think?

44:04.767 --> 44:07.019
They can't put together
an operation

44:07.103 --> 44:09.313
in a matter of hours,
especially if it involves

44:09.397 --> 44:11.315
crossing the Pak border.

44:11.399 --> 44:12.859
It's seven miles across.

44:12.942 --> 44:15.444
It's two minutes' flying time
for Christ sake.

44:15.528 --> 44:17.363
And assaulting a site
they haven't scouted.

44:17.446 --> 44:19.907
‐ I'll scout it.
‐ Great, yeah.

44:19.991 --> 44:21.367
Intel from a rogue agent

44:21.450 --> 44:22.827
running around
with a Russian spy,

44:22.910 --> 44:23.953
using his satellite phone
to communicate.

44:24.036 --> 44:26.414
Do you know who else
is listening to this call?

44:26.497 --> 44:28.291
Do you have
the faintest fucking idea?

44:28.374 --> 44:30.668
‐ It's not like that.
‐ No?

44:32.128 --> 44:35.715
People will believe that
when you turn yourself in.

44:36.465 --> 44:39.886
I don't underestimate
the difficulty, I really don't.

44:39.969 --> 44:41.888
But Max is one of ours.

44:41.971 --> 44:43.848
He went up into the Korengal
because we asked him to.

44:43.931 --> 44:49.103
He put his body on the line.
We can't just abandon him.

44:49.187 --> 44:51.480
[breathes deeply]

44:51.564 --> 44:53.232
We're doing everything we can.

44:53.316 --> 44:56.068
♪ gentle music ♪

44:56.152 --> 45:00.072
♪♪♪

45:00.156 --> 45:01.073
[phone beeps]

45:01.157 --> 45:06.204
♪♪♪

45:13.294 --> 45:14.921
They're not coming.

45:15.004 --> 45:16.756
I have to go in
and get a closer look.

45:16.839 --> 45:19.008
‐ I told you, we can't.
‐ I'm not asking you to come.

45:19.091 --> 45:20.593
I just have to see
if he's alive even.

45:20.676 --> 45:22.470
‐ Carrie.
‐ I know.

45:22.553 --> 45:24.931
You get into trouble,
I'm leaving.

45:25.014 --> 45:27.016
I know.

45:29.518 --> 45:30.853
I need a gun.

45:48.120 --> 45:50.957
[indistinct chatter]

45:51.040 --> 45:54.252
[indistinct radio chatter]

45:59.090 --> 46:01.259
speaking Dari

46:05.304 --> 46:07.515
Make it fast.

46:09.225 --> 46:11.852
Saul.

46:11.936 --> 46:13.688
‐ Haissam.
‐ Saul.

46:13.771 --> 46:15.690
Last night,
I got the presiding judge

46:15.773 --> 46:18.901
to agree to a continuance,
a delay.

46:18.985 --> 46:23.197
She'll open the case,
announce the charges,

46:23.281 --> 46:25.157
and postpone the actual trial.

46:25.241 --> 46:27.285
Why?

46:27.368 --> 46:28.202
So we can find proof

46:28.286 --> 46:32.123
that you didn't shoot down
the helicopter.

46:32.206 --> 46:34.333
You didn't do this.

46:34.417 --> 46:36.043
You're innocent.

46:37.962 --> 46:42.508
Forty years of war,
no one is innocent.

46:43.426 --> 46:45.261
[door opens]

46:45.344 --> 46:47.013
[man] You have to go.

46:47.096 --> 46:49.181
See you out there.

46:53.102 --> 46:55.980
[door closes, locks]

47:01.235 --> 47:04.363
[indistinct chatter]

47:06.657 --> 47:08.284
[camera shutter clicks]

47:10.828 --> 47:14.415
[sighs]
It's supposed to be empty.

47:14.498 --> 47:15.958
Who are all these people?

47:16.042 --> 47:19.378
Families of people killed
in Taliban suicide bombings.

47:19.462 --> 47:22.214
G'ulom's been bussing
them in since last night.

47:22.298 --> 47:24.759
[door opens]

47:24.842 --> 47:27.928
[angry shouting]

47:44.153 --> 47:47.323
[shouting continues]

47:51.744 --> 47:53.954
[shouting recedes]

47:56.582 --> 47:58.000
[camera shutter clicks]

48:05.508 --> 48:09.136
Where is she?

48:13.516 --> 48:14.725
Jesus.

48:14.809 --> 48:19.355
They switched judges on us.

48:24.527 --> 48:27.988
speaking Dari

48:49.343 --> 48:51.137
What's he saying?

48:51.220 --> 48:52.972
[Latifi] speaking Dari

48:53.055 --> 48:53.597
Scott?

48:53.681 --> 48:57.309
[Latifi] speaking Dari

48:57.393 --> 49:02.189
"This man, the so‐called amir,

49:02.273 --> 49:05.443
has plotted to overthrow
the Islamic Republic."

49:06.777 --> 49:09.655
speaking Dari

49:20.458 --> 49:21.584
[Ryan] "He murdered
President Daoud."

49:21.667 --> 49:24.712
[Latifi] speaking Dari

49:24.795 --> 49:26.380
"He murdered
the American President."

49:26.464 --> 49:29.467
[Latifi] speaking Dari

49:31.594 --> 49:35.848
"He has brought misery
and pain on everyone here."

49:37.308 --> 49:40.436
speaking Dari

49:55.618 --> 49:57.369
"He deserves
a thousand deaths,

49:57.453 --> 49:59.705
but this court
can only give him one."

49:59.788 --> 50:03.542
♪ tense music ♪

50:03.626 --> 50:08.923
♪♪♪

50:09.757 --> 50:12.927
speaking Dari

50:18.140 --> 50:20.100
"Death."

50:20.184 --> 50:21.894
[chaotic shouting]

50:21.977 --> 50:23.437
[camera shutters clicking]

50:23.521 --> 50:28.526
♪♪♪

50:44.166 --> 50:46.835
David, can you hear me?

50:46.919 --> 50:49.296
Just about.
What's happening?

50:49.380 --> 50:50.714
[Saul] G'ulom fucked us.

50:50.798 --> 50:52.466
Switched judges
at the Haqqani trial.

50:52.550 --> 50:54.051
Lasted all of 30 seconds.

50:54.134 --> 50:56.470
‐ Was there a verdict?
‐ What do you think?

50:56.554 --> 50:59.974
Death. They could shoot him
in the next five minutes.

51:00.891 --> 51:01.767
Hayes has to intervene.

51:01.850 --> 51:03.769
[distant shouting]

51:03.852 --> 51:05.062
Do you hear?

51:05.145 --> 51:07.189
Hayes has to get
a stay of execution.

51:07.273 --> 51:11.819
Yeah, well, I don't think
that's gonna happen.

51:11.902 --> 51:13.445
Why the hell not?

51:13.529 --> 51:16.532
G'ulom had a one‐on‐one
with Hayes yesterday.

51:16.615 --> 51:17.491
First thing this morning,

51:17.575 --> 51:19.159
Hayes demands new voices
on Afghanistan.

51:19.243 --> 51:22.580
Guess who's in
the Oval Office right now.

51:22.663 --> 51:23.956
John Zabel.

51:24.039 --> 51:25.916
You can't be serious.

51:26.000 --> 51:28.043
[chaotic shouting, chanting]

51:28.127 --> 51:29.628
Get in there before Zabel
gets his feet under the table.

51:29.712 --> 51:32.506
Make the case.

51:32.590 --> 51:34.967
Haqqani dies,
Afghanistan goes up in flames.

51:35.050 --> 51:38.596
David, you have to tell them.

51:38.679 --> 51:41.098
David, you hear me?

51:41.181 --> 51:44.143
I'm hanging on
by my fingertips here.

51:44.226 --> 51:48.689
The president's asking
who's loyal, who's not?

51:48.772 --> 51:50.983
Even talking to you hurts me.

51:51.066 --> 51:55.696
All I can do right now is stay
close and seem to go along.

51:57.239 --> 51:58.490
Sorry, I gotta go.

51:58.574 --> 52:00.909
What?

52:00.993 --> 52:04.913
[crowd shouting, chanting]

52:17.760 --> 52:18.844
[clears throat]

52:18.927 --> 52:22.389
[woman] Yes, he's busy.

52:22.473 --> 52:25.017
‐ Mr. President.
‐ David.

52:25.100 --> 52:27.561
‐ You know John.
‐ I do.

52:27.645 --> 52:29.188
‐ We just heard from Kabul.

52:29.271 --> 52:32.358
Haqqani guilty,
sentenced to death.

52:32.441 --> 52:34.026
Yes.

52:34.109 --> 52:35.861
I was saying to the president
it took, uh, ten years

52:35.944 --> 52:37.946
to get Osama Bin Laden,
but he avenged

52:38.030 --> 52:41.241
Ralph Warner's murder
in, what, three days?

52:41.325 --> 52:43.160
Well, I can hardly
claim credit.

52:43.243 --> 52:45.204
I think that you can, sir.

52:45.287 --> 52:47.748
It's what that part
of the world understands.

52:47.831 --> 52:52.336
[chuckles] An eye for an eye,
a punch in the fucking nose.

52:53.671 --> 52:55.172
Haqqani will be up
against a wall

52:55.255 --> 52:56.757
before the end of the day,

52:56.840 --> 53:01.470
and then we can start
talking about next moves.

53:04.556 --> 53:05.557
♪ tense music ♪

53:05.641 --> 53:07.643
[Max] Oh, no, no.
No, no, no.

53:07.726 --> 53:10.854
[grunting, groaning]

53:15.442 --> 53:20.489
♪♪♪

53:34.586 --> 53:35.254
[indistinct chatter]

53:35.337 --> 53:38.132
[groaning]
No, no, no, no!

53:38.215 --> 53:40.884
‐ speaking Pashto
‐ [Max] No, no!

53:40.968 --> 53:44.304
[Max grunting, groaning]

53:51.645 --> 53:53.313
speaking Pashto

53:56.108 --> 53:59.278
[Max groaning]

53:59.361 --> 54:02.906
♪♪♪

54:02.990 --> 54:04.575
[groaning]
No‐‐

54:04.658 --> 54:05.784
♪ suspenseful music ♪

54:05.868 --> 54:09.705
speaking Pashto

54:09.788 --> 54:11.790
[Max groaning, choking]

54:11.874 --> 54:15.878
♪♪♪

54:15.961 --> 54:18.964
[groaning]

54:21.967 --> 54:23.552
[groaning, breathing heavily]

54:27.014 --> 54:30.350
[muffled grunting]

54:31.727 --> 54:33.937
No.

54:35.397 --> 54:35.981
No.

54:36.064 --> 54:40.194
[breathing heavily]

54:43.238 --> 54:46.241
♪ gentle music ♪

54:46.325 --> 54:51.371
♪♪♪
